[{"id":"VR871151","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of a photon scattering off an electron. The x and y axes are shown for reference with positive x directed horizontally to the right and positive y directed vertically upward. Two arrows labeled Incident Photon and Scattered Photon are shown on dashed lines that form a right angle. The incident photon arrow is labeled p sub 0 and points horizontally to the right in the positive x direction. The scattered photon arrow points vertically downward in the negative y direction. An arrow labeled Electron points upward and to the right and is labeled with coordinates P sub e comma x, end sub, comma P sub e comma y, end sub. A note states that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871151.g03.svg\"/></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A photon scatters at a <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"90\"><math alttext=\"90\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>90</mn></math></span></span>-degree angle off of an initially stationary electron, as shown in the figure. The photon’s initial velocity is in the positive <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>-direction and its final velocity is in the negative <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y\"><math alttext=\"y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>y</mi></math></span></span>-direction. The electron has a final velocity with positive <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y\"><math alttext=\"y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>y</mi></math></span></span> components. Which of the following correctly ranks the magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"p sub 0\"><math alttext=\"p sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> of the photon’s initial momentum, the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>-component <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"p sub e comma x, end sub\"><math alttext=\"p sub e comma x, end sub\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>p</mi><mtext>e,x</mtext></msub></math></span></span> of the electron’s final momentum, and the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y\"><math alttext=\"y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>y</mi></math></span></span>-component <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"p sub e comma y, end sub\"><math alttext=\"p sub e comma y, end sub\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>p</mi><mtext>e,y</mtext></msub></math></span></span> of the electron’s final momentum?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR871151_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"p sub 0 equals, p sub e comma x, end sub, which is greater than, p sub e comma y, end sub\"><math alttext=\"p sub 0 equals, p sub e comma x, end sub, which is greater than, p sub e comma y, end sub\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>p</mi><mtext>e,x</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>p</mi><mtext>e,y</mtext></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"p sub 0 is greater than, p sub e comma x, end sub, which is greater than, p sub e comma y, end sub\"><math alttext=\"p sub 0 is greater than, p sub e comma x, end sub, which is greater than, p sub e comma y, end sub\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>p</mi><mtext>e,x</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msu